emails.body_text:
Hi Leslie,

I want to flag that Zara Mitchell (EMP-1190) had 3 single-day HFWA uses in April (prior to her bereavement leave which starts April 8). This triggers our monitoring threshold.

As a reminder, HFWA protects employees from adverse action based on use of sick leave. I'm documenting in the tracker. No action required from you.{SIG}

Hi,

Quick note: Theo Mbeki (EMP-1126) reported 2 single-day FMLA intermittent uses (March 16 and 18) under LC-2026-0017. Because these are FMLA-designated, they should NOT be counted against his HFWA balance.

However, Theo did have 2 single-day HFWA uses in February (before the FMLA case was designated Feb 20). Those 2 uses are legitimate HFWA draws. I have corrected the tracker to only count Feb uses against HFWA.{SIG}

Hi,

FAMLI log verified — all Q4 2025 cases (Teresa Vang LC-2025-0051, Priscilla Osei LC-2025-0063, Miriam Holloway LC-2025-0043) have confirmed CDLE numbers. Calendar-year caps are being tracked per employee.

No gaps identified.{SIG}

Team,

Effective immediately, please use the updated HFWA tracking column in hfwa_balance_tracker.xlsx: column I "Single-Day Uses — Current Mo." resets at the start of each calendar month. The pattern flag (column J) auto-triggers at 3+ uses.

Note: FMLA-designated absences must NOT be counted against HFWA — confirm this with me before adjusting any employee's balance.{SIG}

Hi Harriet,

Great question. For an approved intermittent FMLA case, you can ask Darius to notify you (and me) as soon as practicable when he needs to use leave — ideally the same day. You cannot require advance notice if the need is unforeseeable.

You cannot ask for the medical reason, but you can require the notification call-out procedure be followed. If he's not following notification procedures, please let me know.{SIG}

Hi Marcus,

Thank you — and yes, please do flag these to me. If Fatima has an underlying health condition driving these absences, she may be entitled to FMLA or HFWA protection and it's better for everyone to have a formal case in place.

I'll reach out to her proactively. Please continue your normal absence notification procedure.{SIG}

Hi Sam,

CDLE received the claim (case FAMLI-CO-2026-51003) and is reviewing. Determination expected within 5–7 business days from April 1, so by approximately April 8–10. Jordan will receive benefit payments directly from CDLE.

In the interim, Jordan should confirm his bank details are up to date with CDLE's employee portal.{SIG}

Hi Raj,

Sending you our Q1 FMLA eligibility matrix for the new cases opened in Feb/Mar. All current cases have been validated as eligible. No borderline cases to flag this quarter.

Note for your awareness: one Supply Chain employee (non-exempt, 0.5 FTE) hired Jan 2021 may hit a borderline hours situation if they file later this year. I'll flag if a case comes in.{SIG}

Hi Dana,

Heads-up: I may be escalating a potential ADA accommodation case soon. Employee is in Finance, diagnosed with mental health conditions, wants workplace adjustments. Not formally filed yet — will send over as soon as the employee submits the request.

Wanted to give you a heads-up so you can calendar it.{SIG}

Hi Isaac,

This is your 30-day follow-up check-in following your return from medical leave on January 27. We want to confirm you are reintegrated well and have no ongoing needs related to your leave or recovery.

If anything comes up, please don't hesitate to reach out. Case LC-2025-0080 is now fully closed.{SIG}

Hi Marcus,

This is your 30-day post-return check-in (you returned February 10). Hope the cardiac recovery is continuing well.

If any work restrictions have changed or you have upcoming medical needs, please reach out. Case LC-2026-0003 is fully closed.{SIG}

Hi Sam,

Once FMLA is designated for Celeste Fontaine, all absences that fall within the certified pattern are FMLA-protected and cannot be counted as attendance occurrences. HFWA single-day uses that occurred before FMLA designation can remain in the HFWA tracker but cannot support adverse action.

Please hold off on any attendance counseling related to Celeste's absences until I confirm the designation status.{SIG}

Hi Jerome,

I have processed your jury duty leave request for November 3–14, 2025. This is paid leave per company policy. Case LC-2025-0082 is open.

Please provide your jury summons to me for the file.{SIG}

Hi Caleb,

Welcome back! Your FMLA leave (October 6–17, 2025) is recorded as fully used under Case LC-2025-0071. You're cleared for full duty.

A 30-day check-in will be scheduled for November 17.{SIG}

Hi Yuki,

Your intermittent FMLA leave is designated under Case LC-2025-0038, effective May 12, 2025 through May 11, 2026. Up to 2 days per month are pre-approved.

Please notify me and your manager each time you need to use leave.{SIG}

Hi Alejandro,

Welcome back from your medical leave. Your FMLA (January 20 – March 14, 2025, LC-2025-0009) has been fully used — 240 hours of your 480-hour annual entitlement. Your rolling FMLA balance resets progressively over the next 12 months.

30-day follow-up check-in: April 14, 2025.{SIG}
